Note: although Lambdin and Kosztarab ( 1977 , p. 205 ) state that they studied paratypes , no holotype was designated by Balachowsky (Daniele Matile, pers. comm.,
April 2015
) and, although the original description refers to " Type : in coll. St. ent. de Paris", it reports a range of adult female body lengths, implying that more than one specimen was measured, and describes the first-instar nymph. Thus, we consider all type specimens (adult and nymphs) in the NMHN to be syntypes and therefore have designated a lectotype .
